Package: AHM
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian DINA Estimation with Unknown Q-Matrix and Attribute Hierarchy
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2026-06-23
Authors@R: person("Xue", "Wang", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                  email = "wangx625@nenu.edu.cn")
Maintainer: Xue Wang <wangx625@nenu.edu.cn>
Description: Implements Bayesian MCMC estimation for the DINA cognitive
    diagnosis model when both the Q-matrix and the attribute hierarchy are
    unknown. The package estimates item slipping and guessing parameters,
    examinee attribute profiles, latent class probabilities, the Q-matrix, and
    the attribute hierarchy. It also includes post-processing for attribute
    label switching, Gelman-Rubin Rhat diagnostics, DIC-based chain selection,
    posterior point estimates, simulation utilities, and an ECPE real-data
    example.
